title: Grateful Dead Live at Calaveras County Fairgrounds on 1987-08-23
lineage: DAT (Sony PCM-R500) > Sound Devices 744T > wav 16/44; Joe Noel Edits: Track, Flac & Pack: Wave > Audacity > flac 16/44; Checksum & tags created in xACT; (Admin note: the info file indocates that these files are 44.1kHz; they are actually 48kHz)
description:
Set 1

Box Of Rain, Jack Straw, West L.A. Fadeaway, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, High Time, Walkin' Blues, Iko Iko*, All Along The Watchtower*

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Playing In The Band-> Drums-> Jam-> I Need A Miracle-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Playing In The Band-> Morning Dew

Encore: Not Fade Away-> Brokedown Palace

* With Carlos Santana, Guitar

David Lindley & El Rayo-X Then Santana Opened

"Mountain Aire Music Festival"

reviews.review_text:
Just Exactly Perfect You want this recording.

I can count on my fingers the number of audience sources that compare.
-Every instrument  clear and well placed.
-Vocals at the perfect level with every singer clear and present.
-An exceptionally wide stereo field. Even the drummers are very distinct from each other. (You just don't get this on an audience recording.)
-The sounds from each instrument and the vocals are balanced to perfection.
-There is no over saturation, distorting echo or weird panning effects.

Compared to the Ultra Matrix, which is also excellent, this recording more than holds it's own.
